genome-wide analogue of the best-hit-per-sequence convention of
\code{\link[=motif_peaks]{motif_peaks()}}) and counts hits in the near zone. \code{"anchors"} counts
the fraction of anchors that have at least one nearby hit; it has no
clean analytical null, so \code{method = "permutation"} is recommended and
\code{method = "binomial"} falls back to a Poisson occupancy approximation
(anti-conservative when hits cluster).
